Types of Modes in python
  Interactive mode: used when an user wants to run one single line or one block of code, it cant be saved.
  Script mode: we write our code in a text file then save it with a . py extension.
Datatypes
  Character: A single letter
  String: A set of characters
  Integer: Whole numbers
  Float: Numbers with decimal points
  Boolean: Represents one of the two values i.e. True or False
